Excellent! Now I have all the information needed. Let me compile a comprehensive summary for you:

## Project Structure Summary for Emoji Picker Screen

### 1. Full-Screen View Architecture

Based on **ClipboardHistoryView.tsx**, full-screen views follow this pattern:

**State Management:**
- Local state for `query` (search text), `filterValue` (for SearchDropdown), `selectedIndex`, and `actionsOpen`
- Uses `useMemo` to compute filtered items based on query and filters
- Sections are flattened into a single array for List navigation

**Layout Structure:**
```
SearchBar (with query, placeholder, dropdown filter, breadcrumbs)
├── SearchDropdown (dropdown filter)
├── Body (.command-palette__body)
│   └── List Container
│       ├── EmptyState (when no results)
│       └── List + ListSections + ListItems
├── ActionPanel (contextLabel, actions array, dropdown sections)
├── Alert (if alert state exists)
└── HUDContainer (for toast-like notifications)
```

**Keyboard Shortcuts:**
- Use `useKeyboardShortcut` hook with `{ key, meta?, shift?, ctrl?, alt? }` object
- Register custom shortcuts like Cmd+K for actions, Cmd+C for copy, etc.
- Shortcuts close the actions dropdown and reset state

**Selection & Navigation:**
- `selectedIndex` tracks current item, bounded by `useEffect` when count changes
- `onActiveIndexChange` fires when user navigates, resets `actionsOpen`
- `onAction` fires on Enter, typically performs primary action
- `activeDescendantId` for a11y: `list-item-${selectedIndex}`

---

### 2. Mock Data File Structure

From **clipboard_data.ts**:

```typescript
export interface ClipboardEntry {
  id: string;
  content: string;
  contentType: 'text' | 'link' | 'color' | 'image';
  sourceApp: string;
  sourceIcon: ReactNode;  // Icon component from icons/
  copiedAt: Date;
  pinned: boolean;
}

export const MOCK_CLIPBOARD_ENTRIES: ClipboardEntry[] = [
  {
    id: 'clip-1',
    content: '...',
    contentType: 'text',
    sourceApp: 'Terminal',
    sourceIcon: TerminalIcon(),  // Instantiated icon component
    copiedAt: new Date(now - 1000 * 60 * 2),  // Relative timestamps
    pinned: true,
  },
  // ... more entries
];
```

**Pattern:** Define a type interface, then export a `MOCK_*` const array. Use icon components imported from `src/components/icons/`.

---

### 3. App.tsx Navigation Wiring

**View Type Discriminated Union:**
```typescript
type NavViewData =
  | { type: 'grid' }
  | { type: 'clipboard' }
  | { type: 'snippets' }
  | { type: 'detail'; item: ListItemData };
```

**Push New Screen:**
```typescript
const nav = useNavigationStack<NavViewData>('Raycast');
const { push } = nav;

// To open a new view:
push('Clipboard History', { type: 'clipboard' });
push('Color Picker', { type: 'grid' });
push('Snippets', { type: 'snippets' });
push(item.title, { type: 'detail', item });
```

**Detecting Full Views:**
```typescript
const isFullView = viewType === 'clipboard' || viewType === 'snippets';
// Full views hide SearchBar and ActionPanel in App.tsx
// They render their own internal UI
```

**State Reset on Pop:**
- `useEffect` with `nav.stackDepth` dependency resets `query`, `selectedIndex`, filters, etc. when popping back to root

**View Rendering:**
```typescript
function renderCurrentView() {
  const entry = nav.currentEntry;
  switch (entry.data.type) {
    case 'clipboard':
      return <ClipboardHistoryView />;
    case 'snippets':
      return <SnippetManagerView />;
    case 'grid':
      return <ColorPickerView ... />;
    case 'detail':
      return <DetailView ... />;
  }
}
```

---

### 4. Grid Component API

**From grid.tsx:**
```typescript
interface GridProps {
  children: ReactNode;
  itemCount: number;
  columns?: 3 | 4 | 5 | 6;  // Default: 4
  onActiveIndexChange?: (index: number) => void;
  onAction?: (index: number) => void;
}
```

**From GridItem (grid_item.tsx):**
```typescript
interface GridItemProps {
  index: number;
  icon?: ReactNode;
  title: string;
  subtitle?: string;
  onClick?: () => void;  // Optional local click handler
}
```

**Keyboard Navigation (built-in to Grid):**
- ArrowRight/Left: Move horizontally, wraps to next/previous row
- ArrowUp/Down: Move vertically, wraps to top/bottom
- Enter: Calls `onAction(activeIndex)`
- Auto-scrolls active item into view with `scrollIntoView({ block: 'nearest' })`

**Grid Context:**
- Used internally; GridItem reads `activeIndex`, `setActiveIndex`, `columns` from context
- GridItem highlights with `grid-item--active` class when `activeIndex === index`
- `data-grid-index` attribute for DOM queries

**Styling:**
- CSS variable `--grid-columns` set on root div for responsive layout
- Role: `listbox`, GridItem role: `option`, aria-selected

---

### 5. Available Icons

From **src/components/icons/index.ts**, available icon components:

**App Icons:**
```
CalculatorIcon, ChatIcon, ClipboardIcon, CpuIcon, EmojiIcon, 
FigmaIcon, PaletteIcon, SafariIcon, SlackIcon, SnippetsIcon, 
TerminalIcon, VscodeIcon, WindowIcon
```

**Arrow Icons:**
```
ArrowDownIcon, ArrowLeftIcon, ArrowRightIcon, ArrowUpIcon
```

**Chevron Icons:**
```
ChevronDownIcon, ChevronLeftIcon, ChevronRightIcon, ChevronUpIcon
```

**Control Icons:**
```
CheckIcon, CircleIcon, DotIcon, EllipsisIcon, MinusIcon, PlusIcon
```

**Action Icons:**
```
CopyIcon, DownloadIcon, DuplicateIcon, EditIcon, PasteIcon, 
RefreshIcon, TrashIcon, UploadIcon
```

**Object Icons:**
```
CalendarIcon, ClockIcon, DocumentIcon, FolderIcon, GearIcon, 
GlobeIcon, HeartIcon, KeyIcon, LinkIcon, LockIcon, StarIcon
```

**Status Icons:**
```
BatteryIcon, BoltIcon, CloudIcon, WifiIcon
```

**Usage:** `import { EmojiIcon } from '../../components/icons'` then render as `<EmojiIcon />`

---

### 6. Key Patterns to Follow

**Component Structure:**
1. Separate `.tsx` component file and `.scss` style file
2. Local state hooks at top: useState, useMemo, useCallback
3. Custom hooks: useNavigation, useKeyboardShortcut, useHUD, useAlert
4. Render JSX with semantic HTML (role, aria- attributes)

**Filtering Pattern:**
```typescript
const filtered = useMemo(() => {
  let items = initialData;
  if (filterValue !== 'all') {
    items = items.filter(item => item.category === filterValue);
  }
  if (query) {
    items = items.filter(item => 
      item.field.toLowerCase().includes(query.toLowerCase())
    );
  }
  return items;
}, [initialData, filterValue, query]);
```

**Selection Management:**
```typescript
useEffect(() => {
  if (selectedIndex >= filteredItems.length && filteredItems.length > 0) {
    setSelectedIndex(filteredItems.length - 1);
  } else if (filteredItems.length === 0) {
    setSelectedIndex(0);
  }
}, [selectedIndex, filteredItems.length]);
```

**SearchBar + Dropdown + List Pattern:**
- SearchBar onChange → update query state → filter items → reset selectedIndex
- Dropdown onChange → update filterValue state → filter items → reset selectedIndex
- Both trigger filter → list re-renders with new filtered data

**ActionPanel Pattern:**
```typescript
const dropdownSections: DropdownSection[] = useMemo(() => [
  {
    title: 'Actions',
    actions: [
      {
        label: 'Copy',
        shortcut: <Kbd keys={['⌘', 'C']} />,
        onClick: handleCopy,
      },
    ],
  },
], [selectedEntry, handleCopy]);

return (
  <ActionPanel
    contextLabel="Screen Name"
    actions={[
      { label: 'Open', shortcut: <Kbd keys={['↵']} /> },
      { label: 'Actions', shortcut: <Kbd keys={['⌘', 'K']} />, onClick: toggleActions },
    ]}
    dropdownOpen={actionsOpen}
    dropdownSections={dropdownSections}
    onDropdownClose={closeActions}
  />
);
```

**For Full Views:**
- Export as standalone view component (e.g., EmojiPickerView)
- Handle own SearchBar, List/Grid, ActionPanel, keyboard shortcuts
- Receive no props from App; use useNavigation hook if needed to pop back
- Render SearchBar (top), body with List/Grid (middle), ActionPanel (bottom)
- Must handle empty state with EmptyState component
- Register global keyboard shortcuts with useKeyboardShortcut

---

### Types Available

From **types.ts**:
```typescript
// For List items
interface ListItemData {
  id: string;
  title: string;
  subtitle?: string;
  icon?: ReactNode;
  accessories?: ListItemAccessoryData[];
  detail?: ListItemDetailData;
}

// For Grid items
interface GridItemData {
  id: string;
  title: string;
  subtitle?: string;
  icon?: ReactNode;
}

interface ColorItemData extends GridItemData {
  color: string;
  category: ColorCategory;  // 'warm' | 'cool' | 'neutral'
}
```

---

This architecture enables you to:
- Create a self-contained EmojiPickerView with its own state
- Push it via `push('Emoji Picker', { type: 'emoji' })` after adding to NavViewData union
- Use Grid or List for layout (Grid recommended for emojis)
- Implement filtering by category/search
- Add keyboard shortcuts (Cmd+C to copy emoji, etc.)
- Show HUD notifications on actions
- Handle navigation back via Escape key in SearchBar

